  <subsection xml:id="subsec-cleaning-reason-1">
    <title> Cleaning Reason 1 </title>

    <p>
      When you put things away were they belong, it makes it easier to find them later. It's 
      just that simple. 
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-cleaning-reason-2">
    <title> Cleaning Reason 2 </title>

    <p>
      Leaving things out and about everywhere becomes a safety hazard. If not put away the cords 
      of power tools become tripping devices, and anything with a blade could cut and injure 
      someone. Or a piece of 2x4 could fall over htting someone in the head. Also, if things
      aren't put away, power tool batteries have a habit of dissapearing.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-cleaning-reason-3">
    <title> Cleaning Reason 3 </title>

    <p>
      If you don't put things away it is well within the scope of disimplary action of tech head 
      to tell people not doing work, goofing off, or just for not helping regularly clean, to continue 
      cleaning the shop until it is clean, become a tempurary cleaner for other people, or just be 
      removed from tech.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <conclusion>
    <title> Thoughts on Cleaning </title>
    
    <p>
      Another way to think about it is just that being smart and cleaning is good for both you
      and everyone else. Now how to help 
      <xref ref="sec-daily-checklist" text="custom">keep things clean on the dailey</xref>
      or 
      <xref ref="sec-cleaning-days" text="custom">how to clean up after someone messes</xref>  
      will be talked about in the next 2 sections
    </p>
  </conclusion>
</section>